 class UMLGMETagValidator
          Validates the GME Project tags found within the model passed in as a parameter GME Project Tags include: NCI_GME_XML_NAMESPACE: Used on Project, Package, and Class UML elements NCI_GME_XML_ELEMENT: Used on Class UML elements NCI_GME_XML_LOC_REF: Used on Attribute UML elements NCI_GME_SOURCE_XML_LOC_REF: Used on Association UML elements NCI_GME_TARGET_XML_LOC_REF: Used on Association UML elements Validation rules are as follows: Package name should not contain spaces Model should not contain duplicate classes Class name should be present Class name should not contain empty spaces Class name should start with a character Navigable association end must have a role name Association end must not contain spaces Association end name should start with a character Associated class should be present in the included package and not excluded Association can not be made to classes in java.lang and java.util packages Class should not contain duplicate associations (association ends which are not navigable are not counted) Attribute name should be present Attribute name should not contain empty spaces Attribute name should start with a character Class should not have duplicate attributes Parent class of any class should be in the included package and not excluded
 class UMLLogicalModelValidator
          Validates the logical model (Object model) of the model passed in as a parameter Validation rules are as follows Package name should not contain spaces or hyphens Model should not contain duplicate classes Class name should be present Class name should not contain empty spaces Class name should start with a character Navigable association end must have a role name Association end must not contain spaces Association end name should start with a character Associated class should be present in the included package and not excluded Association can not be made to classes in java.lang and java.util packages Class should not contain duplicate associations (association ends which are not navigable are not counted) Attribute name should be present Attribute name should not contain empty spaces Attribute name should start with a character Class should not have duplicate attributes Attribute type should be present Attribute type should not contain empty spaces Attribute type should be one of the valid values Parent class of any class should be in the included package and not excluded
 class UMLModelMappingValidator
          Validates the mapping between logical model (Object model) and data model of the model passed in as a parameter Validation rules are as follows Only one table should be present for each of the root level classes There should not be a duplicate entry between the table and a class Every class should have an attribute which is mapped to the primary key column in the database All the attributes in the class should be mapped to corresponding columns in the table There should not be any duplicate tag values in the tables corresponding to attribute of association mapping
